==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Homophone
<hw>Hom"o*phone</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>homophone</ets>. See <er>Homophonous</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A letter or character which expresses a like sound with
another.</def> <rj><au>Gliddon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A word having the same sound as another, but
differing from it in meaning and usually in spelling; <as>as,
<xex>all</xex> and <xex>awl</xex>; <xex>bare</xex> and <xex>bear</xex>;
<xex>rite</xex>, <xex>write</xex>, <xex>right</xex>, and
<xex>wright</xex>.</as></def></p>

<p><ent>Homophonous</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Homophonic</ent>⟦br⟧
